'''Marc Pubill Pagès''' (born 20 June 2003) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] or [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

==Club career==
===Levante===
Born in [[Terrassa]], [[Province of Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Pubill represented [[CE Manresa]], [[RCD Espanyol]], [[Club Gimnàstic de Manresa]] and [[Levante UD]] as a youth.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esportbase.valenciaplaza.com/2021/08/05/estos-son-los-juveniles-que-hacen-la-pretemporada-con-el-atletico-levante/ |title=Estos son los juveniles que hacen la pretemporada con el Atlético Levante |trans-title=These are the youngsters who make the pre-season with Atlético Levante |publisher=esportbase media |language=es |date=5 August 2021 |accessdate=20 December 2021}}</ref> On 13 December 2020, while still a youth, he made his senior debut with the latter's [[Atlético Levante UD|reserves]] by playing the last 11 minutes of a 1–0 [[Segunda División B]] home loss against [[Hércules CF]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.superdeporte.es/levante-ud/2020/12/13/derrota-deja-atletico-levante-situacion-53077127.html |title=Otra derrota que deja al Atlético Levante en una situación muy delicada |trans-title=Another defeat that leaves Atlético Levante in a very delicate situation |publisher=[[Super Deporte]] |language=es |date=13 December 2020 |accessdate=21 December 2021}}</ref>

Pubill scored his first senior goal on 17 October 2021, netting the B's third in a 3–0 away win over the same opponent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.superdeporte.es/levante-ud/2021/10/17/atletico-levante-asesta-golpe-confianza-58476213.html |title=El Atlético Levante asesta un golpe de confianza ante el Hércules (0–3) |trans-title=Atlético Levante certify a confidence blow over Hércules (0–3) |publisher=Super Deporte |language=es |date=17 October 2021 |accessdate=21 December 2021}}</ref> On 3 December, he renewed his contract with the club until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.levanteud.com/es/info/marc-pubill-renueva-su-contrato-con-el-levante-ud-hasta-2026 |title=Marc Pubill renueva su contrato con el Levante UD hasta 2026 |trans-title=Marc Pubill renews his contract with Levante UD until 2026 |publisher=Levante UD |language=es |date=3 December 2021 |accessdate=20 December 2021}}</ref>

Pubill made his first team – and [[La Liga]] – debut on 20 December 2021, starting in a 4–3 home loss against rivals [[Valencia CF]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/levante-vs-valencia/cronica/2021/12/20/61c0c63246163f4f2e8b4589.html |title=Guedes condena a un desgraciado Levante |trans-title=Guedes condemns an unfortunate Levante |publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=es |date=20 December 2021 |accessdate=21 December 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/12/20/primera/1640037271_072001.html |title=Aprobados y suspensos del Levante: Otro fiasco en el ilusionante debut de Pubill |trans-title=Levante's approved and suspended: Another fiasco in Pubill's promising debut |publisher=[[Diario AS]] |language=es |date=20 December 2021 |accessdate=21 December 2021}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 5 February 2023, netting the opener in a 2–1 [[Segunda División]] away win over [[FC Cartagena]].

===Almería===
On 9 August 2023, Pubill signed a six-year contract with [[UD Almería]] in the top tier.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticias/el-almeria-ficha-a-uno-de-los-jugadores-mas-deseados-en-el-mercado-marc-pubill |title=El Almería ficha a uno de los jugadores más deseados en el mercado: Marc Pubill |trans-title=Almería sign one of the most wanted players in the market: Marc Pubill |publisher=UD Almería |language=es |date=9 August 2023 |accessdate=9 August 2023}}</ref> He scored his first [[La Liga]] goal in a 1–1 away draw with [[Granada CF|Granada]] on 18 February 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/674252/almeria-granada |title=Granada 1–1 Almería |publisher=ESPN |date=18 February 2024 }}</ref> He was a regular starter during [[2023–24 La Liga|his first season]] at the club, suffering relegation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/en/news/ud-almeria-say-goodbye-to-202324-season-with-firm-intention-of-returning-to-primera |title=UD Almería say goodbye to 2023/24 season with firm intention of returning to Primera |publisher=UD Almería |date=27 May 2024 }}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 22 July 2025, [[Atlético Madrid]] announced that they had reached an agreement with Almería for the transfer of Pubill. He signed a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |date=22 July 2025 |title=Oficial: Marc Pubill, nuevo lateral derecho del Atlético hasta 2030 |trans-title=Official: Marc Pubill, Atlético's new right-back until 2030 |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2025/07/22/atletico-marc-pubill.html |accessdate=22 July 2025 |publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-la-ud-almeria-para-el-traspaso-de-marc-pubill |title=Acuerdo con la UD Almería para el traspaso de Marc Pubill |trans-title=Agreement with UD Almería for the transfer of Marc Pubill |publisher=Atlético Madrid |language=es |date=22 July 2025 |accessdate=22 July 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 5–1 away defeat against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] on the final matchday of the [[2025–26 La Liga|2025–26 season]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Beren |first=Jeremy |url=https://www.intothecalderon.com/atletico-madrid-columns/25630/villarreal-atletico-de-madrid-takeaways-la-liga-griezmann-alvarez-simeone |title=Villarreal CF 5-1 Atlético de Madrid: Takeaways |publisher=Into The Calderon |date=25 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Pubill represented [[Spain national football team|Spain]] at [[Spain national under-19 football team|under-19 level]], receiving his first call-up to the side in October 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://valenciabase.com/marc-pubill-levante-ud-se-incorpora-a-la-lista-de-convocados-de-espana-sub-19/ |title=Marc Pubill, Levante UD, se incorpora a la lista de convocados de España sub-19 |trans-title=Marc Pubill, Levante UD, joins the list of the called up for Spain under-19 |publisher=Valencia Base |language=es |date=22 October 2021 |accessdate=20 December 2021}}</ref>

He made his debut for the [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21]] team in March 2024, featuring as a starter in a [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] match against [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium]].<ref>{{cite web|title=1-0: Spain U21 and Marc Pubill triumph at the Power Horse Stadium|url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/en/news/1-0-spain-u21-and-marc-pubill-triumph-at-the-power-horse-stadium|publisher=[[UD Almería]]|date=27 March 2024}}</ref> In May 2025, he was included in the squad for the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|final tournament]] in Slovakia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lista de Santi Denia para preparar el Europeo de Eslovaquia|trans-title=Santi Denia's squad list to prepare for the European Championship in Slovakia|language=es|url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/lista-de-Santi-Denia-para-preparar-el-Europeo-de-Eslovaquia|publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]]|date=26 May 2025}}</ref>

Pubill received a call-up to the [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain U23]] team for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]] in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Santi Denia da la lista con los 18 futbolistas para París 2024 y deja como suplentes a Iturbe, Juanlu, Mosquera y Camello|trans-title=Santi Denia announces the list of 18 players for Paris 2024 and leaves Iturbe, Juanlu, Mosquera and Camello as substitutes|language=es|url=https://www.rtve.es/deportes/20240710/juegos-olimpicos-paris-2024-lista-definitiva-espana-futbol/16181491.shtml|publisher=[[RTVE]]|date=10 July 2024}}</ref> He scored the country's first goal in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament – Group C|Group C]] match against [[Uzbekistan national under-23 football team|Uzbekistan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Marc Pubill se convierte en goleador olímpico y sigue aumentando su caché|trans-title=Marc Pubill becomes Olympic goalscorer and continues to increase his stock|language=es|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/almeria/2024/07/24/66a13f7ae2704eae0d8b4591.html|first=Antonio|last=Martínez|publisher=MARCA|date=24 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Marc Pubill, héroe de España ante Uzbekistán|trans-title=Marc Pubill, Spain's hero against Uzbekistan|language=es|url=https://cadenaser.com/andalucia/2024/07/24/marc-pubill-heroe-de-espana-ante-uzbekistan-ser-almeria/|first=Alejandro|last=Peña|publisher=Cadena SER|date=24 July 2024}}</ref> He later appeared as a starter in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament final|gold medal match]] against the host, [[France national under-23 football team|France]], which Spain won by 5–3 [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|after extra time]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Marc Pubill logra con España la medalla de oro|trans-title=Marc Pubill wins the gold medal with Spain|language=es|url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticias/marc-pubill-logra-con-espana-la-medalla-de-oro|publisher=UD Almería|date=10 August 2024}}</ref>

In May 2026, he was named in Spain's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/los-26-que-buscaran-volver-reinar-en-el-mundial |title=Los 26 que buscarán volver a reinar en el Mundial |trans-title=The 26 who will seek to reign again in the World Cup |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |date=May 25, 2026 |access-date=May 25, 2026 |language=es |url-status=live |archive-date=May 25, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260525152452/https://rfef.es/es/noticias/los-26-que-buscaran-volver-reinar-en-el-mundial}}</ref>

